<rss version="2.0" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:ss="http://contenthub.aol.com/slideshow/"><channel><title><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></title><link/> https://www.engadget.com/ <description><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></description><language> en-US</language><copyright>版权所有雅虎 2023</copyright><pubDate> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 20:28:37 +0000</pubDate><generator>雅虎 http://yahoo.com </generator><item><title><![CDATA[Federal judge narrows scope of antitrust case against Google ahead of trial]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>谷歌刚刚在<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-us-justice-department-antitrust-competition-announcement-144344497.html">针对该公司的一项反垄断案件</a>中获得了部分缓刑。联邦法官阿米特·梅塔 (Amit Mehta) <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/08/04/technology/google-search-monopoly-judge.html?smid=nytcore-ios-share&amp;referringSource=articleShare">裁定</a>，司法部 (DOJ) 和主要州不能声称谷歌通过在搜索结果中推销自己的产品而不是其他产品来保护垄断地位。根据裁决，原告尚未证明存在“反竞争效应”。梅塔法官还驳回了有关 Android 兼容性和反碎片协议、Google Assistant、物联网设备和 Android 开源项目的反垄断指控。</p><p>梅塔法官表示，司法部仍然可以提出剩余的论点。值得注意的是，官员们声称谷歌正在滥用权力，要求安卓制造商预装谷歌应用程序，并使谷歌成为其移动浏览器中的默认搜索引擎。美国司法部和各州担心这会阻碍 Bing 和 DuckDuckGo 等竞争对手获得广泛采用。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>谷歌全球事务总裁肯特·沃克在给 Engadget 的一份声明中表示，该公司欢迎法官在驳回搜索问题时的“仔细考虑”。他坚称，人们选择谷歌只是“因为它有帮助”，而且该公司将在审判中证明其其他做法既具有竞争力又合法。我们已要求司法部发表评论，如果收到回复，我们会通知您。</p><p>美国司法部和合作伙伴州于 2020 年提起诉讼。他们当时并未主张采取具体处罚措施，但处罚措施可能包括罚款、业务限制和将部门拆分为独立的公司。当时，谷歌为自己辩护，称它仍然需要谈判合作伙伴关系，并且面临来自 Twitter（现在的 X）和 Expedia 等服务的竞争。</p><p>这并不是针对谷歌的唯一反垄断案件，包括在美国。 2020 年，一个国家联盟因<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-antitrust-lawsuit-texas-attorney-general-204043354.html">涉嫌反竞争广告定价</a>而起诉谷歌。然而，缩小范围可能会使案件变得更加困难，更不用说限制潜在的损害了。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/federal-judge-narrows-scope-of-antitrust-case-against-google-ahead-of-trial-202837725.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/federal-judge-narrows-scope-of-antitrust-case-against-google-ahead-of-trial-202837725.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 619fcfc8-7f19-46c1-bb83-21db0efb0e28</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 04 Aug 2023 20:28:37 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691180920</ingested><modified> 2023-08-04T20:28:44+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Business]]></category><category><![CDATA[Company Legal & Law Matters]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="3862" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/977afb60-3300-11ee-af7b-6257b1650ab1" width="5856"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3862" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/977afb60-3300-11ee-af7b-6257b1650ab1" width="5856"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Justin Sullivan via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[MOUNTAIN VIEW, CALIFORNIA - MAY 10: Alphabet CEO Sundar Pichai delivers the keynote address at the Google I/O developers conference at Shoreline Amp